title: `$view::set()`
description: Force to replace view ID or file path with new file path.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
View::set($id, $path = null);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
View::get('foo.bar'); // return nothing

View::set('foo.bar', '.\lot\asset\php\view.php');

View::get('foo.bar'); // return the `.\lot\asset\php\view.php` value.
~~~

~~~ .php
View::get('.\lot\asset\php\view.php'); // return the `.\lot\asset\php\view.php` value.

View::set('.\lot\asset\php\view.php', '.\lot\asset\php\view-2.php');

View::get('.\lot\asset\php\view.php'); // return the `.\lot\asset\php\view-2.php` value.
~~~